The course includes introduction of the School of Economics and Business Administration, overview of the curricula and regulation of the studies. Students get knowledge and experience on how to use UT IT-systems and academic databases as well as requirements for written papers and proper citing. Students will get overview of different internship opportunities.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to introduce general studies practices at the School of Economics and Business Administration, study regulations, access to IT systems and scientific databases. APA requirements for written papers are introduced and practiced.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will: - know the structure of the curricula and are familiar with organisation and regulation of studies; - know the structure of the School of Economics and Business Administration (of University of Tartu) and can use its webpage; - know how to use different IT systems and study and research related databases; - know the requirements for written papers in the School of Economics and Business Administration and can format them correctly; - can cite the sources properly and avoid plagiarism.
